    <p></p>
  </div>

  <div class="right">
    <h3>
      WHAT if the medium fails to disappear by using a non-normative way of generating perception,
      by taking advantage of the error/glitch derived by the medium itself?
    </h3>

    <div class="content">
      <p>
        <span class="bold uppercase">Real Mirror</span>
         is an interactive object that transforms the viewer's self-image into new, spatial and
        physical forms of perception. The constructed virtual space is based on a VR system that is
        accessible through smart glasses. The interface between body and virtual space - a
        navigation sphere - provides a virtual 360° view of the environs and reacts on spectator’s
        movements of the sphere. In these rooms the user can navigate and lose him/herself at the
        same time. An interplay between two influencing dynamics: the changing environment,
        triggered by one's own movement in space.
      </p>

